HEADWORD: Parovarium
<hw>Par`o*va"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Para-</er>, and <er>Ovarium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
group of tubules, a remnant of the Wolffian body, often found near the
ovary or oviduct; the epoophoron.</def>⟦br⟧
